00:46:48.700 --> 00:46:54.190 align:middle line:84%
So tell us just what you would
say in brief for any one of us

00:46:54.190 --> 00:46:56.320 align:middle line:84%
who is in the process
of losing someone

00:46:56.320 --> 00:46:59.050 align:middle line:84%
or soon will lose someone
to their transition out

00:46:59.050 --> 00:47:00.250 align:middle line:90%
of physical view.

00:47:00.250 --> 00:47:02.435 align:middle line:90%
We know they're still with us.

00:47:02.435 --> 00:47:04.060 align:middle line:84%
Tell us what we can
do to have the most

00:47:04.060 --> 00:47:06.640 align:middle line:90%
effective communication.

00:47:06.640 --> 00:47:09.640 align:middle line:84%
>>DILLARD: Well, the first thing
is to allow yourself to grieve.

00:47:09.640 --> 00:47:11.830 align:middle line:90%
Allow yourself to grieve.

00:47:11.830 --> 00:47:13.150 align:middle line:90%
Don't try to make it fast.

00:47:13.150 --> 00:47:16.300 align:middle line:84%
Don't try to think
yourself through it.

00:47:16.300 --> 00:47:17.420 align:middle line:90%
Pour your heart out.

00:47:17.420 --> 00:47:18.220 align:middle line:90%
Open your heart.

00:47:18.220 --> 00:47:20.440 align:middle line:84%
Feel all the grief,
all the sadness.

00:47:20.440 --> 00:47:25.060 align:middle line:10%
As much as you can handle, let
it up, because it's the grief--

00:47:25.060 --> 00:47:27.910 align:middle line:10%
behind that grief as it
comes up, there's space.

00:47:27.910 --> 00:47:29.170 align:middle line:10%
There's opening.

00:47:29.170 --> 00:47:31.960 align:middle line:10%
And in that opening, you can
ask for the love of the heavens

00:47:31.960 --> 00:47:34.660 align:middle line:10%
to fill you, for the
comfort of the heavens.

00:47:34.660 --> 00:47:36.910 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
transformation also.

00:47:36.910 --> 00:47:40.090 align:middle line:84%
And to speak and talk
to your loved ones.

00:47:40.090 --> 00:47:41.770 align:middle line:90%
Again, courage.

00:47:41.770 --> 00:47:43.840 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes we-- oh, we can't.

